[TOOL CALLING INSTRUCTIONS]
To call a tool, add it to `tool_calls`, providing its `name` and arguments
categorized by their source:
- `literal_args`: JSON string of literal values (e.g. {"query": "Kaval AI"}).
- `planner_context_args`: JSON string mapping tool argument names to `call_id`s
  of previous tool calls whose output you want to reuse.
- `input_args`: JSON string mapping tool argument names to keys of the context
  variables listed above.
Each argument name must appear in only ONE category. Set a `call_id` so you can
reference the result in later steps. The output of each tool call is recorded in
the steps below.

When you have enough information to answer, set `output` to the final result and
leave `tool_calls` empty.

